Reasoning: The paper discusses the use of formal logics and automated reasoning in modeling ethical theories for autonomous systems, which falls under the category of artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper specifically focuses on a quantified modal logic, which is a subfield of mathematical logic (cs.LO). The use of logic in modeling ethical theories also has implications for cybersecurity (cs.CY) and robotics (cs.RO), as autonomous systems may need to make ethical decisions in these domains. Finally, the paper discusses an algorithm for proof automation, which falls under the category of software engineering (cs.SE).
